XTCPgps is a plugin for X-Plane. Based on Ed Park's XMAPgps, It sends NMEA sentences
over TCP connection to mapping software: GPRMC, GPGGA, dummy GPGSA.

Demonstrated to work with XCSoar 7.2 running on Android,
XCSoar running on a Linux and Jeppesen's FlightDeck running in Parallels Windows 7.


Pre-requests:
- Installed X-Plane 11
- Installed python 3


Stage 1:
Install Python 3 plugin framework for X-Plane, following
https://xppython3.readthedocs.io/en/stable/usage/installation_plugin.html

Copy PI_XTCPgps.py to X-Plane/Resources/plugins/PythonPlugins



Stage 2:
Edit X-Plane/Resources/plugins/PythonPlugin/PI_XTCPgps.py on line 39,
set Host and Port for your NMEA client.

Stage 3:
Start your NMEA client, Start X-Plane.


If nothing happens make sure the plugins are enabled in X-plane -> plugins



